messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Digest Number 374
messages.messageBody:
<<Now in the South and missing Trader Joes, the waterfront in Portland,
Good
Earth (at Clackamas Town Center), the Gorge and the MOUNTAINS!!!>>

The Good Earth is gone! *sob* They had some of the best food I've ever
eaten and I miss them. Seeing the Gorge still takes my breath away, I
never get tired of taking guests there. My mom and I will be going to
The Maryhill Museum Of Art this August, she wants to take me there so we
can have some time alone. All I can think about is how much the kids
would get out of the trip.

Kris

AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< I have visions of weeks and weeks with no sun.
Is that the case? How do you adjust? Do you get depressed? >>

I know you didn't ask me Isabel..but as a former Portland lover, now living
in Florida, I feel qualified!!:)
Yes.
No.
Yes.
How's that for blunt? I can handle the rain, love rain actually. But the day
after day of grey sky and drizzle I hated. No can do.
Ren

messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Digest Number 374
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 5/20/02 7:10:59 PM Central Daylight Time, AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 5/20/02 7:10:59 PM Central Daylight Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< This Oregon talk has me missing the place. I lived in Portland and
Forest Grove and drove every weekend to sleep on the beach at Pacific
City's Cape Kiwanda. >>


Ooooh, another former Portlander!! sigh....
I used to go into Forest Grove with my Grandma to swim laps. My Dad graduated
from the HS there......they live on a farm in Manning. Do you know where that
is? It's very obscure, mainly was farms in old times.
If you're heading to the beach it's the turn off just before that Dairy Queen
on Hwy. 26...Hayward road. Beautiful country.
Ren
